==English==

===Etymology===
From Old French ''[[ma]] [[dame]]'', "my lady". ''[[ma]]'' is from Latin ''[[mea]]'', feminine form of "my"; ''[[dame]]'' is from Latin ''[[dama]]'', "lady", "woman".

===Noun===
'''madam''' (''plural:'' '''mesdames''')
# [[polite]] form of [[address]] for a [[woman]]
# the [[mistress]] of a [[household]]
#(''colloquial'') [[conceited]] or [[quarrelsome]] [[girl]]
#:''Get to your room, madam!''
# (''U.S.A. only?'') [[woman]] who runs a [[brothel]]

